# UI layer (`src/accounting_anomaly/ui/`)

See **[AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md)** for full project context.

When changing UI code:

- Delegate parsing, classification, and persistence to `core/` and `db/`; avoid duplicating business logic in widgets.
- Follow existing patterns: `QMainWindow` / `QDialog` subclasses, signals for user actions, table models in `transaction_table.py`.
- GUI behavior is not covered by automated tests; note manual verification steps in your response when UI flow changes.
- Headless test runs use `QT_QPA_PLATFORM=offscreen` (see AGENTS.md); local manual run: `accounting-anomaly`.
